# 1. お世話になっている人達に

Kanade: *Nod* The bridge transitions into the last chorus seamlessly now...
Kanade: I might actually be able to finish this demo before Mafuyu comes back from school.
Kanade: Just a little bit more to—
Kanade: Oh...
Kanade: (I didn't have lunch today...)
Kanade: (I should eat something... But I also want to finish what I'm doing...)
Kanade: Wait, I know...
Kanade: (Those chocolate the others gave me for Valentine's Day should be... Ah, here they are.)
Kanade: Mmm... They're so good...
Kanade: (How many people did I receive chocolates from in the end?)
Kanade: (There's Ena, Mizuki...and Ms. Mochizuki... I really need to thank them again.)
Kanade: Oh, wait a second...
Kanade: White Day is coming up...
Kanade: I should do something to give back to all of them. So, Ena, Mizuki, Ms. Mochizuki and...
Kanade: Actually...
Kanade: This is a good opportunity for me to give back to everyone who always supports me...
Kanade: Which includes Miku and the others... And Hoshino...
Kanade: Okay, I think that's everyone.
Kanade: Actually, hold on...
Kanade: What am I supposed to give them exactly?
Kanade: That was delicious.
Mafuyu: Yes, it was.
Kanade: You can stay seated. I'll wash the dishes.
Mafuyu: Okay, thank you...
Kanade: Wait, Mafuyu, are you leaving for school already? I was hoping to ask you a quick question...
Mafuyu: A quick question?
Kanade: I'd like to give back to everyone who's been supporting me on White Day, but I'm not sure what to get them.
Kanade: Which is why I was wondering if you already know what you're going to give people.
Mafuyu: My plan is to buy some snacks or sweets at a store. Most places are holding White Day fairs around this time.
Kanade: I see... Do you have a particular store in mind?
Mafuyu: Not yet... Probably some place that people are talking about, or one that simply catches my attention.
Kanade: I see...
Kanade: Thank you. That helps a lot.
Mafuyu: You're welcome.
Kanade: (I guess it's normal for people to give each other storebought gifts...)
Kanade: (It'd be nice to make something again. I really liked those scented candles I made with Ms. Mochizuki and the others...)
Kanade: (But I doubt I'll be able to make anything all on my own... And it would probably be hard to get together as a group again.)
Kanade: (Which means buying something may be my best option.)
Kanade: (But I want to give everyone something they'd actually want. Something that'd make them happy...)
Kanade: Alright, I'll try asking them what they want.
Mizuki: <Alright, I'm gonna log off now since this seems like a good place to stop!>
Ena: <Me too. My sketch is done, so I'm gonna go to bed.>
Kanade: <Thank you both for your hard work.>
Kanade: <Oh, wait... Can I ask you two something before you go?>
Ena: <Huh? What's up?>
Kanade: <I'm thinking about getting everyone something for White Day. What would you two like to have?>
Mizuki: <I dunno. There's so much...!>
Ena: <Hmm... Cheesecake is my go-to... But if it's you getting me something, K, then... Hmm...>
Mizuki: <Oh, you could get me one of Kinsendo's limited-edition chocolate cakes♪>
Kanade: <Uhh... A limited-edition chocolate cake from Kinsendo... Got it.>
Ena: <Wait a second! They only make ten of those each year, Amia! How do you expect her to get her hands on one?!>
Kanade: <Oh, is that true...?>
Mizuki: <Haha. Sorry! I thought I'd just try floating it out there.>
Mizuki: <To be honest, K, I'll be happy with whatever you give me.>
Ena: <Me too. Choose whatever you feel is right.>
Kanade: <Okay, I'll do that... Thank you both.>
Kanade: <How about you, Yuki?>
Mafuyu: <I'm also okay with whatever.>
Kanade: <O-Okay... Thank you.>
Kanade: ...
Kanade: (They're all okay with whatever I get...?)
Kanade: (So, what do I get them...?)
Mizuki: <Anyway, I'm logging off. See you all later!>
Ena: <Me too. Don't work too hard, K, Yuki.>
Kanade: <Oh... Okay.>
Mafuyu: <Good night.>
Mafuyu: I'll go pour us some tea.
Kanade: Okay, thank you.
Kanade: (I'll need to think about this some more...)
Kanade: A message? Who's sending me one at this hour...?
Kanade: Huh? Hoshino?
